<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-2345] One should not have to explicitly provide the service/port for cxf is there&apos;s only one</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-2345</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is due to the following code in &lt;tt&gt;Client createClient()&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;CxfEnpoint&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
            ObjectHelper.notNull(portName, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Please provide endpoint/port name&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
            ObjectHelper.notNull(serviceName, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Please provide service name&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
            ClientFactoryBean factoryBean = createClientFactoryBean();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When there&apos;s only one service/port, we should just use it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
